# Part 2 — Describe a time when you had a problem with using an electronic device

I’d like to talk about a time when I had a serious problem with my laptop about half a year ago. It happened in my university dormitory late at night, just one day before an important programming assignment was due. As a computer science student, I rely heavily on my laptop for coding and studying, so the situation was extremely stressful for me.

The problem started when my laptop suddenly froze while I was debugging a C++ project. At first, I thought it was just a temporary lag, but after restarting it several times, the screen remained black and the system wouldn’t boot properly. I became really anxious because all my project files and notes were stored on that device, and I hadn’t backed them up yet.

At the beginning, I tried solving the issue by myself. I searched for solutions on my phone and watched several technical videos online. After that, I entered the BIOS system and ran a hardware check. Eventually, I discovered that the SSD had become loose, probably because I had accidentally dropped my backpack a few days earlier.

Luckily, one of my classmates was quite good at repairing computers. He helped me open the back cover of the laptop and reconnect the SSD carefully. After restarting the device again, it finally worked normally. I was honestly so relieved that I almost shouted in excitement.

This experience taught me two important lessons. First, I realized how dependent we are on electronic devices nowadays. Second, I understood the importance of backing up files regularly. Since then, I’ve started using cloud storage to save my important documents automatically.

### 中文翻译：

我想谈谈大约半年前我笔记本电脑出问题的一次经历。那天晚上我正在大学宿舍里学习，而且第二天就是一个重要编程作业的截止日期。作为一名计算机专业学生，我非常依赖电脑写代码和学习，所以当时真的特别焦虑。

问题发生在我调试一个 C++ 项目的时候。我的电脑突然卡死了。一开始我以为只是暂时卡顿，但重启了几次后，屏幕依然是黑的，系统也无法正常启动。我当时特别慌，因为所有项目文件和笔记都存在里面，而且我还没有备份。

一开始我尝试自己解决。我用手机搜索解决方案，还看了不少技术视频。后来我进入 BIOS 做硬件检测，最后发现是 SSD 松动了，可能是因为前几天我不小心摔了一下书包。

幸运的是，我有一个同学很擅长修电脑。他帮我打开电脑后盖，小心地重新连接了 SSD。重新启动之后，电脑终于恢复正常了。我当时真的特别激动，甚至差点喊出来。

这次经历让我学到了两件事。第一，我意识到现代人对电子设备依赖非常严重。第二，我明白了定期备份文件的重要性。从那以后，我开始使用云存储自动保存重要文件。

